### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

The point is to have 2 different Angular apps, parent and child.
Child should be embedded into parent view as customElement, BUT to have an Injection context of parent application. When child application was created and `createCustomElemen()` was called right after ,js file with child element uploaded - user can easily create and render child element in some container of parent applications and no error occurs. But in that case we do not have an ability to provide our parent Injection context to the child app.
If move that application creation logic into parent application and load child one as a regular js module, it creates fine, but on attempt to render that component into view you will always face an error that `inject()` must be called inside Injection context because of Angular's StandaloneService:

```typescript
  static ɵprov = /** @pureOrBreakMyCode */ /* @__PURE__ */ defineInjectable({
    token: StandaloneService,
    providedIn: 'environment',
    factory: () => new StandaloneService(inject(EnvironmentInjector)),
  });
```  
In second scenario that inject will be called outside of injection context for some reason and will throw an error.


In provided git link I've implemented 2 scenarios (you can switch them commenting in and out some lines). Main files to view is: `parent/src/app/app.component.ts` and `/child/src/web-component.ts`

Piece of example:
in parent application
```typescript
  private container = viewChild('customSelectorContainer', { read: ViewContainerRef });
  private envInjector = inject(EnvironmentInjector);

  ngOnInit() {
    this.loadScript().then(({ emConfig, emComponent }) => {
      const customElement = createCustomElement(emComponent, { injector: this.envInjector });
      customElements.define('child-app', customElement);

      const childElement: HTMLElement = this.renderer.createElement('child-app');
      // Here comes an error:
      this.container()?.element.nativeElement.appendChild(childElement);
    });
  }

  private loadScript(): Promise<{ config: ApplicationConfig, component: Type<any> }> {
    const src = 'http://127.0.0.1:5500/dist/child/main.js';
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
      const scriptElement = document.createElement('script');
      scriptElement.src = src;
      scriptElement.type = 'module';

      let emConfig: ApplicationConfig;
      let emComponent: Type<any>;

      scriptElement.onload = () => {
        import(src)
          .then(({ emConfig: config, emComponent: component }) => {
            emComponent = component;
            emConfig = config ;
            return this.zone.runOutsideAngular(() => createApplication(config));
          })
          .then(appRef => resolve({ emConfig, emComponent }))
      }
      document.body.appendChild(scriptElement);
    });
  }
```

